docs.name: Andrew Yule & Co. Ltd. (526173)
docs.description: Andrew Yule & Co. Ltd. is an India-based company. The Company's operating segments include Engineering, Electrical and Tea. The Company's Engineering segment is engaged in the manufacturing of industrial fans, air pollution and water pollution control equipments and turn-key projects. The Electrical segment is engaged in the manufacture of high temperature (HT) and low temperature (LT) switchgears, transformers, relay and contactors, turn-key projects on power distribution. Its Tea segment is engaged in tea growing and manufacturing. The Company's subsidiaries include Hooghly Printing Company Limited, Yule Engineering Limited and Yule Electrical Limited.

docs.name: PCISX: Prudential International Value Fund Class C
docs.description:
The investment seeks long-term capital growth.
 The fund invests primarily in the common stock and preferred stock of foreign (non-U.S. based) companies of all sizes. It normally invests at least 65% of total assets in common stock and preferred stock of foreign companies in at least three different countries, without limit as to the amount of fund assets that may be invested in any single country. The fund may invest anywhere in the world, including North America, Western Europe, the United Kingdom and the Pacific Basin, but generally not in the U.S. The manager uses a value investment style when deciding which securities to buy for the fund.

docs.description: Vakif Gayrimenkul Yatirim Ortakligi AS is a Turkey-based company engaged in real estate operations and investments. The Company leases and rents commercial and office buildings in Ankara and Istanbul, and develops real estate projects. It invests in real estates for development purposes. The Company's projects include Ankalife Yasam Kompleksi and Bakirkoy Is Merkezi. Among its real estate portfolio are Kavakli Vakif Is Merkezi, Levent Is Merkezi, Kadikoy Is Merkezi, Bagdat Caddesi Magaza, Mustafakemalpasa Dukkan, Kavaklidere Dukkan, Finans Market Is Merkezi and Vakif Is Merkezi. Vakif Gayrimenkul Yatirim Ortakligi AS is a subsidiary of Turkiye Vakiflar Bankasi TAO and Toplu Konut Idaresi Baskanligi (TOKI).

docs.name: Fastnet Oil & Gas PLC (FAST)
docs.description: Fastnet Oil & Gas Plc (Fastnet), formerly Sterling Green Group Plc, is a non-trading holding company. The Company is an independent oil and gas exploration company focused on identifying early stage exploration and appraisal opportunities in Offshore Ireland and Africa. Its aim is to assemble a portfolio of high impact conventional oil and gas assets that delivers sustainable growth and value for the Company. During the fiscal year ended March 31, 2012, it had two offshore licensing options in the Celtic Sea and an interest in a net profit bonus arrangement relating to the Connemara prospects offshore Ireland. On December 21, 2011, the Company's subsidiary, Taxdebts Limited was disposed. The Company's subsidiaries include Sterling Green Limited, which is engaged in Debt management and Sterling Green (Mortgages) Limited, which is engaged in re-mortgaging.

docs.description:
The investment seeks to maximize total return.
 The fund normally invests at least 80% of net assets plus borrowings for investment purposes in a diversified portfolio of securitized obligations of any kind. It invests primarily in securities that are investment grade and may invest up to 15% of total assets in bonds that are below investment grade, which are commonly referred to as 'high yield' or 'junk' bonds. The fund may invest in certain types of derivative instruments for hedging and investment purposes.
